    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but you're saying it's not about mercy. i don't know... it feels like it is. if someone is suffering like this, and there's absolutely no way to fix it, why is holding on considered the \"right\" thing? it feels so cruel to force someone to stay in a body that's just a vessel for agony. if there's no hope for relief, isn't seeking an end the most compassionate way to handle it?",
